 South Africa is without a doubt, a sport-loving country but since the ’95 Rugby World Cup, a nation has never displayed as much spirit and unity. The Match in Africa, that took place on home soil, at the Cape Town Stadium on 7 February, saw a world record number of spectators after 51 945 tennis lovers flocked to the pavilions. The exciting match between Roger Federer and Rafael Nadal was in service of the South African nation and the two Grand-Slammers put frills aside for the purpose of entertainment. Spectators were blown away by a game of doubles showcasing the local comedian, Trevor Noah and tech mogul, Bill Gates. Whether you bought your tickets to watch live or tuned in on television, it’s a guarantee that you watched the game. Share your experience of the Match in Africa with us and send us an email to sjani@mobserver.co.za.